      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm working on a research paper and i think i keep using passive voice too much. can u help me identify it and show me how to fix it? like if i have a sentence like \"the data was collected by the researchers\" how do i make it better?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The passive voice can be a sneaky thing, isn't it? I'd be happy to help you identify and fix it. The example you gave, \"the data was collected by the researchers,\" is a classic case of passive voice. You can rephrase it to active voice by making the subject of the sentence do the action. For instance, \"the researchers collected the data.\" This revised sentence is much clearer and more direct, don't you think? \n\nIt's a bit like a goblin trying to hide in a pile of leaves – the passive voice can make it hard to see what's really going on. But by making the subject do the action, you're like a brave adventurer uncovering the hidden treasure, and your writing becomes much more engaging and effective.",
