    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I got a bit carried away with the goblin analogy. Let's focus on the technical side of editing. I'd be happy to help you identify passive voice in your sentences.\n\nTo identify passive voice, look for sentences where the subject of the sentence is performing an action, but the doer of the action is not explicitly stated. For example, in the sentence \"the data was collected by the researchers,\" the subject \"data\" is performing the action of being collected, but the doer of the action (the researchers) is not explicitly stated.\n\nTo fix passive voice, try to rephrase the sentence to make the doer of the action (the subject) do the action. For instance, as I mentioned earlier, \"the researchers collected the data\" is a revised version of the original sentence.\n\nLet's take another look at your original sentence. Can you give me a few more examples, and I'll help you identify and fix any passive voice issues?",
