      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay thanks. i get the idea. here is another one: \"the results were analyzed using a t-test.\" how would i rewrite that to be active? also are there any specific words that usually signal passive voice so i can find them myself?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The sentence \"the results were analyzed using a t-test\" is another example of passive voice. To fix it, you can rephrase it to make the subject (the results) do the action. Here's a revised version: \"The researchers analyzed the results using a t-test.\"\n\nAs for specific words that signal passive voice, here are a few common ones to look out for:\n\n* \"was\" (or other forms of \"to be\" verbs like \"were\", \"been\", etc.)\n* \"was\" followed by a verb ending in -ed (e.g., \"was analyzed\", \"was written\", etc.)\n* \"to be\" verbs in the passive voice are often preceded by words like \"had\", \"had been\", \"will have been\", etc.\n* \"by\" (this can be a giveaway for passive voice, as it often indicates that the action is being performed by someone or something else)\n* \"of\" (this can also be a hint, as it often indicates that the action is being performed on something or someone)\n\nKeep in mind that these are not hard and fast rules, and there are many exceptions. But being aware of these words and phrases can help you identify passive voice and make the necessary changes",
      "source": "target",
